www.Addic7ed.com

01:19.358 --> 01:21.326
Well, I'm glad that you're all excited

01:21.328 --> 01:22.994
about the corporate retreat.

01:22.996 --> 01:25.171
A special shout-out
to the legal department

01:25.174 --> 01:28.299
who just settled the lawsuit
from last year's retreat.

01:28.301 --> 01:31.135
I'm looking at you, Wendy,
Ms. Black-out-and-get-naked.

01:31.137 --> 01:33.304
That is not the order

01:33.306 --> 01:35.039
it happened in.

01:35.041 --> 01:36.343
No, it was not.

01:36.346 --> 01:39.310
I hope everyone used my
checklist of what to bring.

01:39.312 --> 01:41.045
I did! Oh, crap.

01:41.047 --> 01:42.437
I forgot my positive attitude.

01:42.440 --> 01:45.717
Lucky for you, I brought
plenty for everybody.

01:45.719 --> 01:47.919
Anyways, I made sure
the retreat will have

01:47.921 --> 01:49.721
all of your favorite things.

01:49.723 --> 01:50.989
Parasailing.

01:50.991 --> 01:52.523
Rum tasting.

01:52.525 --> 01:54.525
Sitting by the pool and judging people.

01:54.527 --> 01:56.728
That's when they're at
their most vulnerable.

01:56.731 --> 01:59.382
And a little something for everybody...

01:59.385 --> 02:00.765
karaoke!

02:00.767 --> 02:03.001
No, no.

02:03.003 --> 02:04.168
Karaoke?

02:04.170 --> 02:06.004
More, like, kara-no-ke.

02:11.411 --> 02:13.845
Fine. At least wear
the matching t-shirts

02:13.847 --> 02:16.047
with personalized catchphrases
I made for everybody.

02:16.049 --> 02:18.049
I don't have a catchphrase.

02:18.051 --> 02:20.018
Oh. She's good.

02:20.020 --> 02:23.054
So? Let's go! Everyone on the buses!

02:23.056 --> 02:24.473
both: Yeah!

02:24.476 --> 02:26.057
Uh, everyone except for my group.

02:26.059 --> 02:27.548
We have to wait for Dorothy.

02:27.551 --> 02:29.150
- What?
- Both: No!

02:29.153 --> 02:31.072
Why would you put Dorothy in our group?

02:31.075 --> 02:32.659
Okay, you know she's not gonna
be an asset in the tug of war,

02:32.661 --> 02:33.932
I'll tell you that right now.

02:33.934 --> 02:35.633
My job is to look out for everybody.

02:35.635 --> 02:37.669
Oh, uh, uh... Dorothy
can ride in my chopper.

02:37.671 --> 02:39.270
I mean, she's so old,

02:39.272 --> 02:41.105
maybe I'll just drop her off in heaven.

02:41.107 --> 02:42.473
Okay.

02:42.475 --> 02:45.109
- Wow.
- The V-Man is on fire.

02:45.111 --> 02:47.138
You know,
it just came to me.

02:47.141 --> 02:47.997
I don't know.

02:48.000 --> 02:50.113
All right, but seriously,

02:50.116 --> 02:51.683
she can't ride in my chopper.

02:51.685 --> 02:53.918
<i>♪</i>

02:53.920 --> 02:56.120
Jackie, can you come in here, please?

02:59.125 --> 03:01.292
<i>♪</i>

03:01.294 --> 03:02.994
You wanted something?

03:02.996 --> 03:06.164
No...

03:06.166 --> 03:09.000
but an overweight man in
Ohio wants that shirt back.

03:09.002 --> 03:11.002
It's from Talbots.

03:11.004 --> 03:13.371
Hey-ah!

03:13.373 --> 03:15.606
Are they feeding you
jokes via an earpiece?

03:15.608 --> 03:17.008
No...

03:17.010 --> 03:18.176
No?

03:18.178 --> 03:19.412
All right, fine.

03:19.415 --> 03:21.179
The corporate retreat
is my only opportunity

03:21.181 --> 03:23.181
to get face time with the big dogs.

03:23.184 --> 03:26.350
Gabe and Noah over here wrote
for "The Harvard Lampoon,"

03:26.353 --> 03:28.386
and they were executive story editors

03:28.389 --> 03:30.355
on "The Suite Life of Zack & Cody."

03:30.357 --> 03:32.790
What a great use of a Harvard education.

03:32.792 --> 03:35.860
We can't all go to Bad
Life Choices University.

03:37.464 --> 03:38.997
That's right, I said...
I mean, they said it,

03:38.999 --> 03:41.799
but then I said it.

03:41.801 --> 03:44.836
In your face!

03:44.838 --> 03:47.205
<i>♪</i>

03:47.207 --> 03:49.240
You forgot to assign homework!

03:49.242 --> 03:51.242
God, even in your
dreams, you're still you.

03:51.244 --> 03:52.625
I know.

03:52.628 --> 03:53.937
I'm exhausted.

03:53.940 --> 03:56.180
That's why I need this retreat so bad.

03:56.182 --> 03:57.982
I'm just gonna get there, chill out,

03:57.984 --> 04:00.051
and make sure Wendy sleeps on her side.

04:00.053 --> 04:01.819
Why do you do so much for these people?

04:01.821 --> 04:03.888
- They're like children.
- No, they're not so bad.

04:03.890 --> 04:05.356
199, 200!

04:05.358 --> 04:08.126
A new record!

04:08.128 --> 04:10.294
Emily, we're out of post-its!

04:10.296 --> 04:12.897
Okay, maybe they are
a little like children.

04:12.899 --> 04:15.066
All the more reason
why I need to be the one

04:15.068 --> 04:16.798
who keeps the train running.

04:16.802 --> 04:21.105
Even though Emily-bot needs
her batteries recharged.

04:21.107 --> 04:23.508
I'm gonna let that go
because you're tired.

04:23.510 --> 04:26.077
Emily, when are we leaving?

04:26.079 --> 04:29.714
I wanna be a-floatin' on a lazy river.

04:29.716 --> 04:31.082
And I have to pee,

04:31.084 --> 04:33.918
but I'm holding it for the lazy river.

04:33.920 --> 04:35.416
Lazy rivers are corny.

04:35.419 --> 04:38.089
I'm going to an artisanal honey
tasting hosted by Ira Glass.

04:38.091 --> 04:40.525
Oh, I'm your friend, and even
I wanna beat you up right now.

04:40.527 --> 04:42.527
Guys, we're a team.

04:42.529 --> 04:44.095
We have to wait for Dorothy,

04:44.097 --> 04:46.330
even though she's super late.

04:46.332 --> 04:49.167
I don't wanna have to
give away her t-shirt.

04:49.169 --> 04:52.537
She does say that a lot.

04:52.539 --> 04:54.705
Trust me, no one needs
to get out of this office

04:54.707 --> 04:56.007
more than me.

04:56.009 --> 04:57.542
We just have to wait a few more...

04:58.945 --> 05:00.945
Which alarm is that?

05:00.947 --> 05:03.381
- Zombie virus?
- Alien invasion?

05:03.383 --> 05:05.249
Giant spider robots

05:05.251 --> 05:07.418
from another dimension
where the Nazis won?

05:07.420 --> 05:09.220
No, that one goes,
"Ee-yoo-ee-yoo-ee-yoo."

05:09.222 --> 05:10.855
Oh.

05:10.857 --> 05:13.191
- It's a gas attack.
- Ugh.

05:13.193 --> 05:14.502
<i>Breaking News:</i>

05:14.505 --> 05:16.229
<i>Supervillain, and documentary star,</i>

05:16.232 --> 05:17.651
<i>Dr. Psycho, has just released</i>

05:17.654 --> 05:20.264
<i>an unknown toxic gas into Charm City.</i>

05:20.266 --> 05:23.047
<i>The mayor urged citizens to stay indoors</i>

05:23.050 --> 05:24.850
<i>as his limousine pulled away.</i>

05:24.853 --> 05:27.438
Scientists estimate that it
will take at least 12 hours

05:27.440 --> 05:29.073
for the gas to disperse.

05:30.346 --> 05:32.076
Who'd have thought
someone named Dr. Psycho

05:32.078 --> 05:34.245
would be capable of something like this.

05:34.247 --> 05:35.246
All right, everyone.

05:35.248 --> 05:37.645
Doctor Psycho.

05:37.648 --> 05:38.896
He went to medical school.

05:38.898 --> 05:40.497
We should get on the bus.

05:40.499 --> 05:42.499
It says that if the gas
reaches critical levels,

05:42.501 --> 05:44.735
the whole building will go into lock...

05:44.737 --> 05:48.138
<i>Emergency lockdown procedure initiated.</i>

05:48.140 --> 05:49.506
<i>Stay calm.</i>

05:49.508 --> 05:51.742
I'll take "unknown gas attacks"

05:51.744 --> 05:54.311
for 500, Alex.

05:54.313 --> 05:55.312
Get...

06:04.243 --> 06:08.037
<i>I can't believe they think
it's going to take 12 hours</i>

06:08.040 --> 06:10.040
for the gas to disperse.

06:10.042 --> 06:12.209
That's what they said when Jackie ate

06:12.211 --> 06:14.244
that vending machine burrito.

06:16.015 --> 06:17.414
In yo face!

06:17.416 --> 06:19.850
I can't believe this is happening.

06:19.852 --> 06:22.653
Ugh, I needed this retreat so bad.

06:22.655 --> 06:24.393
Well, if it makes you
feel any better, Emily,

06:24.395 --> 06:25.422
this is all your fault.

06:25.424 --> 06:27.057
If you didn't make us wait for Dorothy,

06:27.059 --> 06:28.576
we'd be on a bus to
Coast City right now,

06:28.578 --> 06:30.861
asking Wendy to stop drawing
penises on people's faces.

06:30.863 --> 06:32.548
Then stop falling asleep.

06:32.551 --> 06:34.264
Oh, my God, Dorothy.

06:34.266 --> 06:36.066
Hey, what if she's stuck
out there in the gas?

06:36.068 --> 06:37.434
Actually...

06:37.436 --> 06:39.236
she's already at the retreat.

06:39.238 --> 06:40.871
Uh.

06:40.873 --> 06:42.105
- Great.
- Okay, this is officially

06:42.107 --> 06:43.423
the worst retreat ever.

06:43.426 --> 06:45.442
Guys, I'm in charge.
Don't freak out, okay?

06:45.444 --> 06:46.677
Relax. Breathe in.

06:46.679 --> 06:48.679
Breathe out.

06:48.681 --> 06:51.081
Oh, my God. My chopper can't
make it because of the gas.

06:51.083 --> 06:52.660
We're all gonna be
stuck in here together.

06:52.662 --> 06:54.551
I'm freaking out!

06:54.553 --> 06:56.753
I can't believe this is happening.

06:56.755 --> 06:58.555
Okay, hold on, hold on.

06:58.557 --> 07:00.147
I can fix this.

07:00.150 --> 07:03.193
Now, there is no reason we
can't have fun and bond here.

07:03.195 --> 07:05.762
You know, I've got my
karaoke machine, and...

07:05.764 --> 07:06.913
All: No!

07:06.916 --> 07:08.949
So that's a maybe on the karaoke,

07:08.952 --> 07:11.969
but give me 20 minutes, and I
will throw something together

07:11.971 --> 07:13.470
you guys will love.

07:13.472 --> 07:15.572
I'd rather take my chances with the gas.

07:15.574 --> 07:17.774
I think we'd all rather you did that.

07:17.776 --> 07:19.885
Ho-ho-ho!

07:19.888 --> 07:23.190
Jackie, could you get that
microphone I just dropped?

07:23.193 --> 07:24.224
Whoops!

07:24.227 --> 07:26.276
You didn't get it because
you know it's not real.

07:26.279 --> 07:28.151
<i>♪</i>

07:28.153 --> 07:29.419
All right.

07:29.421 --> 07:30.888
I didn't have a ton of time,

07:30.890 --> 07:32.422
and these are my backup decorations,

07:32.424 --> 07:33.790
so go easy on me.

07:33.792 --> 07:37.160
Okay, who wants a flaming volcano?

07:37.162 --> 07:38.175
Yep.

07:38.178 --> 07:40.297
I guarantee you'll lava them.

07:42.101 --> 07:44.801
If you want, I can get my
guys to punch that up for you.

07:44.803 --> 07:48.405
And to pass the time, I
have a bunch of fun games.

07:48.407 --> 07:50.440
It'll be just like we're at the retreat.

07:50.442 --> 07:52.042
- So there's kayaking?
- Well, no.

07:52.044 --> 07:53.377
- Parasailing?
- No.

07:53.379 --> 07:54.711
- Wakeboarding?
- No,

07:54.713 --> 07:56.407
and before anyone asks another one,

07:56.410 --> 07:57.976
we are trapped in the office,

07:57.979 --> 08:00.413
the limitations of which
you are very familiar.

08:00.416 --> 08:01.782
Mm-hmm.

08:01.784 --> 08:02.983
White water rafting?

08:02.985 --> 08:04.485
Shut up, Teddy.

08:04.487 --> 08:05.986
I'll tell you what we do have.

08:05.988 --> 08:09.032
Kelly Clarkson's
greatest hits on karaoke!

08:09.035 --> 08:09.990
All: No!

08:09.992 --> 08:11.992
Okay, back in the maybe pile.

08:14.140 --> 08:16.430
You know, this might be
the four volcanoes talking,

08:16.432 --> 08:18.432
but I don't totally hate this.

08:18.434 --> 08:20.167
Yeah, I don't hate this either.

08:20.169 --> 08:22.234
I do hate this, but not as
much as I thought I would.

08:22.236 --> 08:24.805
I'm being told this
is a bad joke area...

08:24.807 --> 08:27.241
anyway, I'm also not
having a hellish time.

08:29.612 --> 08:33.447
Guys, I think we owe
somebody a big thank you.

08:33.448 --> 08:35.149
Awe, guys.

08:35.150 --> 08:36.616
To alcohol!

08:36.619 --> 08:39.620
all: To alcohol!

08:42.220 --> 08:45.210
Well, who wants to play a game
of desert island companion?

08:45.213 --> 08:46.260
Mm!

08:46.263 --> 08:48.229
Is that where you pick someone
to go in a closet with you

08:48.231 --> 08:50.264
for seven minutes to suck face?

08:50.266 --> 08:52.032
'Cause I choose Van.

08:52.034 --> 08:53.534
- Let's go.
- Uh, no.

08:53.536 --> 08:55.054
No, no.

08:55.057 --> 08:57.257
We have no confirmation
that that is the game.

08:57.273 --> 08:58.335
That's not the game.

08:58.338 --> 09:01.542
That is not the game,
Wendy, that is not the game.

09:01.544 --> 09:03.711
You pick one person
you'd wanna be paired with

09:03.713 --> 09:05.913
if you were stranded
on a deserted island.

09:05.915 --> 09:07.254
It's a team building game.

09:07.257 --> 09:08.482
Jackie, who would you pick?

09:08.484 --> 09:09.848
I'd go by myself.

09:09.851 --> 09:12.786
Okay, let's say if you went by yourself,

09:12.788 --> 09:14.154
you would starve to death.

09:14.156 --> 09:15.689
- That's fine.
- Oh.

09:15.691 --> 09:18.125
I'd pick Van because he's rich, and...

09:18.127 --> 09:19.693
people would probably look for him.

09:19.695 --> 09:21.962
Also, I can tell by his brittle nails

09:21.964 --> 09:23.697
that he has an iron deficiency,

09:23.699 --> 09:25.463
so by day ten...

09:25.466 --> 09:27.701
I'd be able to overpower him,

09:27.703 --> 09:29.703
and then I'd eat him.

09:29.705 --> 09:31.972
Piece by piece.

09:31.974 --> 09:35.175
While he was still alive so
that the meat doesn't spoil,

09:35.177 --> 09:37.577
and I could survive long
enough to be rescued.

09:44.586 --> 09:46.153
- Teddy, you're up!
- Well...

09:46.155 --> 09:48.155
Team building is super lame,

09:48.157 --> 09:49.723
but obviously, if I
had to pick somebody,

09:49.725 --> 09:52.726
I would pick my boy,
Ron, because he's my boy.

09:52.728 --> 09:53.827
Awe.

09:53.829 --> 09:55.026
Ron, what about you?

09:55.029 --> 09:57.564
- Oh, I know, I'd pick...
- Go ahead.

09:57.566 --> 09:59.566
- Um...
- Go ahead.

09:59.568 --> 10:01.969
- Jackie.
- Awkward!

10:03.372 --> 10:05.372
How are you not picking me?

10:05.374 --> 10:08.976
It's just that Jackie's
smart and practical, and plus,

10:08.978 --> 10:11.745
she's a mom so you know she
keeps snacks in her purse.

10:11.747 --> 10:13.133
Yeah, but we're best friends.

10:13.136 --> 10:14.815
If we were doing practical,
I would've picked Emily.

10:14.817 --> 10:16.250
Aww, Teddy, that...

10:16.252 --> 10:17.484
But I don't want to
spend time with Emily.

10:17.486 --> 10:19.586
I wanna hang out with my bro!

10:19.588 --> 10:21.422
Fine, look, if you must know,

10:21.424 --> 10:23.824
it's just that nothing's
ever good enough for you.

10:23.826 --> 10:25.159
And if you're on a desert island,

10:25.161 --> 10:26.560
you must remain positive.

10:26.563 --> 10:28.762
There's a reason why Tom
Hanks put a smiley face

10:28.764 --> 10:30.864
- on that volleyball.
- Oh, come on,

10:30.866 --> 10:33.500
at best, that volleyball
looked nonplussed.

10:33.502 --> 10:34.552
He was bewildered.

10:34.555 --> 10:36.337
Well, I wouldn't bring Teddy because

10:36.339 --> 10:38.405
he's too frail to catch or be food.

10:38.407 --> 10:40.407
Well, I would never bring you, Wendy.

10:40.409 --> 10:43.210
And by the way, I have been
blasting my quads lately,

10:43.212 --> 10:44.745
and they are a healthy
dose of lean protein.

10:44.747 --> 10:46.013
- Jackie, feel my thigh.
- No.

10:46.015 --> 10:47.475
- Feel the thigh!
- No!

10:47.478 --> 10:49.550
I told you, I don't want
to eat any of you idiots.

10:49.552 --> 10:50.998
I just want to die alone.

10:51.001 --> 10:53.854
Well, luckily for you, that
is definitely going to hap...

10:53.856 --> 10:55.889
Don't finish that sentence
if you want to live.

10:55.891 --> 10:57.017
Okay, guys,

10:57.020 --> 10:59.092
I think we're missing
the point of the game.

10:59.095 --> 11:00.894
You're supposed to
say something positive.

11:00.896 --> 11:03.530
Well, I'm positive that
Teddy couldn't spear a fish

11:03.532 --> 11:06.100
to save his life.

11:06.102 --> 11:08.302
The hell I can't.

11:08.304 --> 11:11.305
I bet you 50 bucks you
can't throw this tiki torch

11:11.307 --> 11:13.307
hard enough to knock
over that trash can.

11:13.309 --> 11:14.575
Again, not the game.

11:14.577 --> 11:15.876
- You're on.
- Yeah!

11:15.878 --> 11:18.144
Oh, I'm going in on this action.

11:18.147 --> 11:19.947
Oh, God.

11:19.949 --> 11:21.497
All right, give me some
room. Give me some room,

11:21.499 --> 11:23.784
- give me some room.
- All right, all right, all right.

11:23.786 --> 11:25.352
Here we go.

11:27.156 --> 11:29.590
all: Oh!

11:29.592 --> 11:31.158
So, that happened...

11:32.862 --> 11:34.595
<i>Gas breach.</i>

11:34.597 --> 11:36.597
- Oh!
- Follow me!

11:41.934 --> 11:46.170
<i>Gas breach.</i>

11:46.172 --> 11:47.538
<i>Gas breach.</i>

11:51.510 --> 11:53.043
Good thinking, Wendy.

11:53.045 --> 11:54.578
Okay, we should all get the gas masks.

11:54.580 --> 11:56.814
Oh, they're out there.

11:56.816 --> 11:59.616
What? Where?

11:59.618 --> 12:01.519
Why did you bring us in here, then?

12:01.522 --> 12:03.587
Uh, because it has everything we need.

12:03.589 --> 12:06.423
A particle accelerator, a
quantum field synthesizer,

12:06.425 --> 12:09.059
and a bucket where we
can go to the bathroom.

12:09.061 --> 12:11.261
But there's no food or water.

12:11.263 --> 12:13.630
Well, there's that karaoke
machine you love so much.

12:13.632 --> 12:15.265
- Oh, goody!
- Ah, it's broken.

12:15.267 --> 12:16.300
No, it's right...

12:16.302 --> 12:18.469
Oh.

12:18.471 --> 12:19.780
I changed my mind.

12:19.783 --> 12:21.638
I'm picking Teddy for
that desert island thing.

12:21.640 --> 12:23.640
Oh, look at that! Maybe Jackie's my boy.

12:23.642 --> 12:25.676
How dare you! Traitor!

12:25.678 --> 12:28.445
Okay, okay, we are a little stressed.

12:28.447 --> 12:30.114
Now, if we can get the gas masks,

12:30.116 --> 12:32.850
we can get supplies, and
somewhere safe, and...

12:32.852 --> 12:35.452
Who went in the bucket?

12:35.454 --> 12:36.620
You gave me four volcanoes.

12:36.622 --> 12:38.489
I'm only a man.

12:38.491 --> 12:39.690
All right.

12:39.692 --> 12:41.058
It's not a big deal.

12:41.060 --> 12:43.093
One of us will go get the hazmat suit,

12:43.095 --> 12:46.130
grab the gas masks, and come back.

12:46.132 --> 12:48.165
Where are the hazmat suits?

12:48.167 --> 12:49.700
Well, you planned a costume party

12:49.702 --> 12:51.119
the first night of the retreat,

12:51.122 --> 12:54.571
so Dorothy and Randy went as
Walter White and Jesse Pinkman.

12:54.573 --> 12:56.471
Can we focus?

12:56.496 --> 12:58.496
We just need someone
to hold their breath,

12:58.521 --> 13:00.321
and go out there, and get the masks.

13:00.346 --> 13:02.546
We don't know what that
gas will do to my skin,

13:02.581 --> 13:03.947
or my white linen suit.

13:03.949 --> 13:05.234
Well, I shouldn't go.

13:05.259 --> 13:06.934
I'm a bit of a wildcard.

13:06.959 --> 13:08.955
You can't trust what I'll do out there.

13:08.980 --> 13:09.922
Yeah, and we've already established

13:09.924 --> 13:12.389
that I'm totally useless in
a survival situation, so...

13:12.391 --> 13:13.557
Okay, well, that's fine

13:13.559 --> 13:15.592
because I am perfectly happy

13:15.594 --> 13:17.561
staying here and dying alone.

13:17.563 --> 13:19.163
Check, please.

13:21.767 --> 13:23.567
So that happened.

13:23.569 --> 13:25.569
Wait, I already said,
"So that happened."

13:25.571 --> 13:27.571
Uh, Noah's more of the joke guy...

13:27.573 --> 13:29.283
I write the heart moments.

13:29.286 --> 13:30.974
Anyway, he got stuck out in the gas.

13:30.976 --> 13:32.576
The joke guy's dead?

13:32.578 --> 13:34.444
Ah, well, well, well.

13:34.446 --> 13:36.613
Looks like the joke
van's running on empty.

13:38.184 --> 13:39.583
Ruh-roh.

13:39.585 --> 13:40.584
Damn it.

13:40.586 --> 13:41.895
Ruh-roh?

13:41.898 --> 13:43.420
Guys...

13:43.422 --> 13:44.988
where's Emily?

13:44.990 --> 13:47.658
<i>♪</i>

13:47.660 --> 13:49.092
I just need a helmet.

13:49.094 --> 13:50.093
Huh.

13:53.098 --> 13:58.869
<i>♪</i>

13:58.871 --> 14:01.305
This isn't the bathroom bucket, is it?

14:01.307 --> 14:03.674
<i>No, it's another bucket.</i>

14:03.676 --> 14:05.309
<i>Good save.</i>

14:05.311 --> 14:09.880
<i>♪</i>

14:09.882 --> 14:11.656
How do I get these masks down?

14:11.659 --> 14:12.500
<i>Hold on.</i>

14:12.503 --> 14:14.860
<i>Teddy's checking the manual.</i>

14:14.863 --> 14:17.086
Okay, this manual is a mess.

14:17.089 --> 14:19.224
Who wrote this
abomination? John Grisham?

14:19.226 --> 14:21.927
Oh, not even John Grisham
is safe from your wrath, now?

14:21.929 --> 14:23.929
<i>This is why you're not
on my desert island.</i>

14:23.931 --> 14:25.731
You know what, I wouldn't
wanna be on a island with you,

14:25.733 --> 14:27.733
"The Pelican Brief," and
your phony positive attitude.

14:27.735 --> 14:30.936
Guys, can you stop bickering
for one second and focus?

14:30.938 --> 14:32.738
I'm running out of oxygen,

14:32.740 --> 14:34.806
and I'm pretty sure this
is the bathroom bucket.

14:34.808 --> 14:36.975
<i>It is. Over.</i>

14:36.977 --> 14:39.978
You guys are useless.

14:39.980 --> 14:43.982
<i>♪</i>

14:46.720 --> 14:49.488
I got 'em!

14:49.490 --> 14:50.655
<i>Yes!</i>

14:52.092 --> 14:53.658
I'm the funny one!

14:53.660 --> 14:55.727
I'm only partners with that hack

14:55.729 --> 14:58.296
because he lets me live
in his mother's basement.

14:58.298 --> 15:01.466
Her sandwiches are delicious.

15:01.468 --> 15:02.408
<i>Emily, Emily!</i>

15:02.411 --> 15:04.018
<i>Okay, whatever you do, don't...</i>

15:04.021 --> 15:06.070
<i>- Breathe in.</i>

15:06.073 --> 15:07.906
<i>♪</i>

15:12.983 --> 15:16.995
<i>♪</i>

15:16.997 --> 15:18.830
<i>Emily, honey?</i>

15:18.832 --> 15:20.832
Are you okay, sweetie?

15:20.834 --> 15:22.634
Am I okay?

15:22.636 --> 15:24.636
How nice of you to ask.

15:24.638 --> 15:27.005
Oh, she's fine, guys.

15:27.007 --> 15:29.007
Because in all the
time I've worked here,

15:29.009 --> 15:31.009
not one of you selfish bastards

15:31.011 --> 15:33.690
have expressed any
interest in how I feel.

15:33.693 --> 15:36.579
I am like the mother bird
who vomits into your mouths

15:36.604 --> 15:39.374
to keep you alive,
and what do I get back?

15:39.399 --> 15:41.173
Bitch, whining, moaning.

15:41.176 --> 15:43.367
When all I wanted was to
sing a little karaoke, and

15:43.369 --> 15:45.369
to wear cute and thoughtful
matching t-shirts!

15:45.371 --> 15:47.571
Well, if you're too cool to match,

15:47.573 --> 15:50.574
then you're too cool
for matching gas masks.

15:50.576 --> 15:52.209
- All: No!
- No, no, no, no!

15:53.266 --> 15:56.423
I'd like to recant
my earlier assessment.

15:59.474 --> 16:04.843
<i>♪</i>

16:04.868 --> 16:07.445
I feel like it's some kind of anger gas.

16:09.197 --> 16:10.164
Hey, Van,

16:10.189 --> 16:12.409
I have a question for you.

16:12.434 --> 16:14.600
Do you wipe your own ass?

16:14.625 --> 16:18.627
Because I've never seen
you do anything by yourself.

16:18.652 --> 16:20.828
And I hope Wendy does eat you,

16:20.853 --> 16:22.926
because then at least
you'd serve some purpose,

16:22.951 --> 16:25.551
you entitled, iron-deficient,
son of a bitch.

16:27.071 --> 16:28.925
For the record,

16:28.950 --> 16:30.516
I do wipe myself.

16:30.541 --> 16:33.142
I have since I was a little over 30.

16:33.167 --> 16:36.201
- Oh, you showed her.
- Yes.

16:36.226 --> 16:37.571
<i>Star Labs has confirmed</i>

16:37.596 --> 16:40.222
<i>the mysterious fog is truth gas.</i>

16:40.247 --> 16:41.313
Well, that's not so bad.

16:41.338 --> 16:44.459
<i>Exposure to the gas for more
than two hours will, however,</i>

16:44.484 --> 16:46.529
<i>cause a nervous system to shut down,</i>

16:46.554 --> 16:47.862
<i>resulting in death.</i>

16:47.887 --> 16:49.400
<i>Now, for some sports scores</i>

16:49.425 --> 16:51.911
<i>from that lying piece of crap
who will never leave his wife,</i>

16:51.936 --> 16:53.493
<i>Brock Donovan.</i>

16:53.518 --> 16:55.237
You guys probably didn't hear this,

16:55.262 --> 16:58.497
but Emily said if she
died, I get all her stuff.

17:01.701 --> 17:02.934
Emily, honey?

17:02.936 --> 17:04.102
Okay, you gotta come in here.

17:04.104 --> 17:05.260
The gas is gonna kill you.

17:05.262 --> 17:06.872
You know what's killing me?

17:06.874 --> 17:09.508
That none of you ever say thank you.

17:09.510 --> 17:11.910
You know, you complained
about how every retreat sucks,

17:11.912 --> 17:13.878
so I busted my ass to find one

17:13.881 --> 17:16.548
with a artisanal honey tasting.

17:16.550 --> 17:18.517
You know, crapping all
over other people's tastes

17:18.519 --> 17:20.551
does not mean you have any, Teddy.

17:20.554 --> 17:22.521
Your track suits make
you look like Daft Punk

17:22.522 --> 17:23.922
without the helmet!

17:23.924 --> 17:25.723
Ho, ho, ho, ho.

17:25.726 --> 17:27.459
Her mind is gone.

17:27.461 --> 17:28.894
I mean, she's talking nonsense.

17:28.896 --> 17:30.962
- Right, Jackie?
- Emily is not coming in.

17:30.964 --> 17:32.931
Someone's gonna have to go save her.

17:32.933 --> 17:34.733
Normally, that's be Emily.

17:34.735 --> 17:37.202
- Hmm.
- So are you gonna do it?

17:37.204 --> 17:39.604
I came up with the idea,
so I've done my part.

17:39.606 --> 17:42.140
And I also have a good reason.

17:42.142 --> 17:43.386
Damn it.

17:43.389 --> 17:45.258
You guys don't want to
be adults about this?

17:45.261 --> 17:47.979
Maybe duck-duck-goose, or...

17:47.981 --> 17:50.215
All right, okay.

17:50.217 --> 17:51.927
Now, if you get into any trouble,

17:51.930 --> 17:53.930
two tugs and we'll pull you out.

17:53.933 --> 17:56.421
Lure her in with this cherry Danish.

17:59.426 --> 18:01.059
<i>♪</i>

18:02.229 --> 18:08.233
<i>♪</i>

18:10.303 --> 18:12.304
<i>I've got nothing.</i>

18:12.306 --> 18:13.505
<i>Still nothing.</i>

18:13.507 --> 18:15.107
<i>Oh, wait a minute.</i>

18:15.109 --> 18:16.408
<i>I see something.</i>

18:16.410 --> 18:17.642
<i>Oh, hello, Emily.</i>

18:17.644 --> 18:19.077
<i>Would you like a cherry Danish?</i>

18:19.079 --> 18:20.512
Get him!

18:20.514 --> 18:22.314
<i>- Pull me back in, Teddy!</i>
- Go!

18:22.316 --> 18:23.949
- A little help, a little help...
- You got it, you got it!

18:23.951 --> 18:25.117
- You got this.
- A little help?

18:25.119 --> 18:26.418
I'd help, but...

18:26.420 --> 18:27.753
Pull it!

18:27.755 --> 18:28.976
- You've got this!
- <i>I don't want</i>

18:28.978 --> 18:30.855
<i>your stupid cherry Danish!</i>

18:32.459 --> 18:36.862
<i>♪</i>

18:36.864 --> 18:39.331
She was so mean!

18:41.969 --> 18:44.302
Do you think I use my
cuteness as a crutch?

18:44.304 --> 18:45.785
No, Ron.

18:47.774 --> 18:48.956
So now what?

18:48.959 --> 18:52.144
The bathroom bucket's gone,
and Emily's about to die.

18:52.146 --> 18:54.546
We need to fix one of these things.

18:54.548 --> 18:58.784
You know, I'm not usually one
for making speeches, but, uh...

18:58.786 --> 19:01.953
Do you remember what it was
like before Emily came here?

19:01.955 --> 19:03.789
We were all just a bunch of strangers

19:03.791 --> 19:05.957
working in the same office...

19:05.959 --> 19:07.959
but then, a funny thing happened.

19:07.961 --> 19:10.550
A lady named Emily arrived,
and she taught us how to love.

19:10.553 --> 19:11.797
She taught us how to care.

19:11.799 --> 19:14.800
By taking care of all of us.

19:14.802 --> 19:16.901
- Is he doing an accent?
- Yeah.

19:16.904 --> 19:21.039
But she made us a family,
and family means doing...

19:21.041 --> 19:23.946
even if you're doing something
you might not want to do,

19:23.949 --> 19:26.845
but doing it we're gonna do.

19:26.847 --> 19:29.047
And not just for us...

19:29.049 --> 19:31.049
for Emily!

19:31.051 --> 19:33.409
That. Was. Beautiful.

19:36.422 --> 19:39.858
And look at the
instrument I had to play.

19:39.860 --> 19:41.626
Guys, Van...

19:41.628 --> 19:43.862
slash, Gabe, is right.

19:43.864 --> 19:47.032
I think we know the
sacrifice we need to make

19:47.034 --> 19:50.035
to get Emily back in here.

19:50.037 --> 19:52.070
All: Oh,.

19:53.387 --> 19:56.074
<i>♪ Here's the thing, we
started out friends ♪</i>

19:56.076 --> 20:00.078
♪ It was cool, but it was all pretend ♪

20:00.080 --> 20:05.450
♪ Yeah, yeah, since you've been gone ♪

20:05.452 --> 20:08.620
<i>♪ You dedicated, you took the time ♪</i>

20:08.622 --> 20:12.057
♪ It wasn't long till
I called you mine ♪

20:12.060 --> 20:16.187
♪ And that's all you'd
ever hear me say ♪

20:16.190 --> 20:19.758
♪ But since you been gone ♪

20:19.761 --> 20:23.329
♪ I can breathe for the first time ♪

20:23.332 --> 20:25.566
♪ I'm so moving on ♪

20:25.569 --> 20:27.272
♪ Yeah, yeah ♪

20:29.042 --> 20:30.075
Hey, hey...

20:30.077 --> 20:31.402
not this time.

20:35.082 --> 20:37.249
So you really don't remember anything?

20:37.251 --> 20:39.150
No, it's a complete blank.

20:39.152 --> 20:42.306
So, even though we never
made it to Coast City,

20:42.309 --> 20:44.892
you guys really think it was
the best retreat you've ever had?

20:44.895 --> 20:46.157
Oh, for sure.

20:46.159 --> 20:48.193
And it was all thanks to you, Emily.

20:48.195 --> 20:49.761
Thanks, Emily.

20:49.763 --> 20:51.963
Aw, guys, come on. You
don't need to thank me.

20:51.965 --> 20:53.698
Sure.

20:53.700 --> 20:55.656
You know, we appreciate
how much you do for us,

20:55.659 --> 20:57.225
but, like, you don't have to.

20:57.228 --> 20:58.103
You're family.

20:58.105 --> 20:59.905
We love you no matter what.

20:59.907 --> 21:01.907
Plus we'd hate for you
to go all psycho on us.

21:03.677 --> 21:06.577
I don't even know what
that would look like.

21:06.580 --> 21:08.113
But maybe you're right.

21:08.115 --> 21:10.115
I do need to be able to trust you guys,

21:10.117 --> 21:12.117
and that's part of being a family too.

21:12.119 --> 21:14.871
You know, we're thinking
about going to karaoke tonight.

21:14.874 --> 21:16.202
- Do you wanna...
- I'm in!

21:16.205 --> 21:18.382
I love karaoke.

21:18.385 --> 21:19.351
We figured.

21:19.354 --> 21:20.601
Can we sing Kelly Clarkson?

21:20.604 --> 21:22.360
Mm-hmm.

21:22.403 --> 21:23.972
Heh. That's funny.

